Text.SourceString: Morning, <PlayerName>$Player</>! <NPCName>Chef Raj</> has been in the kitchen, cooking up a storm. Breakfast is served!
Text.LocalizedString: Morning, <PlayerName>$Player</>! <NPCName>Chef Raj</> has been in the kitchen, cooking up a storm. Breakfast is served!

Text.SourceString: I made you something special today, <PlayerName>$Player</>. Ta-da!
Text.LocalizedString: I made you something special today, <PlayerName>$Player</>. Ta-da!

Text.SourceString: So, what's the game plan today, <PlayerName>$Player</>? Show me the agenda!
Text.LocalizedString: So, what's the game plan today, <PlayerName>$Player</>? Show me the agenda!

Text.SourceString: <PlayerName>$Player</>... I just want to say that... I love you so much. Please don't ever leave me.//You're the only thing I care about most in the world.
Text.LocalizedString: <PlayerName>$Player</>... I just want to say that... I love you so much. Please don't ever leave me.//You're the only thing I care about most in the world.

Text.SourceString: You're my everything, <PlayerName>$Player</>...
Text.LocalizedString: You're my everything, <PlayerName>$Player</>...

Text.SourceString: I've got a <PlayerName>$Player</>-shaped hole in my heart today, babe... How was your day, by the way?
Text.LocalizedString: I've got a <PlayerName>$Player</>-shaped hole in my heart today, babe... How was your day, by the way?

Text.SourceString: I miss you, babe. How was your day today?
Text.LocalizedString: I miss you, babe. How was your day today?

Text.SourceString: Missed you today, <PlayerName>$Player</>. How was your day?
Text.LocalizedString: Missed you today, <PlayerName>$Player</>. How was your day?

Text.SourceString: Feeling a little drained, babe. I think it's time for me to sleep soon.//<portrait=normal>Don't worry about me though. I, uh, sleep like a log. Enjoy the rest of your evening.
Text.LocalizedString: Feeling a little drained, babe. I think it's time for me to sleep soon.//<portrait=normal>Don't worry about me though. I, uh, sleep like a log. Enjoy the rest of your evening.

Text.SourceString: I woke up to a mountain of snow at our doorstep this morning! I shoveled it up real quick. Let me know if there's more, okay?
Text.LocalizedString: I woke up to a mountain of snow at our doorstep this morning! I shoveled it up real quick. Let me know if there's more, okay?

Text.SourceString: Oh, I've got to check on the roof tomorrow. The rain is pretty hard, and I need to ensure there are no leaks.
Text.LocalizedString: Oh, I've got to check on the roof tomorrow. The rain is pretty hard, and I need to ensure there are no leaks.

Text.SourceString: You wouldn't believe what happened in my home office today! Some water slipped in through the window.//<portrait=sad>I left the window open...totally on me! Lesson learned.
Text.LocalizedString: You wouldn't believe what happened in my home office today! Some water slipped in through the window.//<portrait=sad>I left the window open...totally on me! Lesson learned.

Text.SourceString: Oh, I've got to check on the roof tomorrow. The rain is pretty hard, and I need to ensure there are no leaks.
Text.LocalizedString: Oh, I've got to check on the roof tomorrow. The rain is pretty hard, and I need to ensure there are no leaks.

Text.SourceString: What do you think about us wearing hats tomorrow, babe? Picture us in matching pink ones at the cherry blossom fest.//<portrait=surprised>We'll be like human blossoms!
Text.LocalizedString: What do you think about us wearing hats tomorrow, babe? Picture us in matching pink ones at the cherry blossom fest.//<portrait=surprised>We'll be like human blossoms!

Text.SourceString: But...I don't have a pink hat. Not sure if I'm up for buying one just for this.
Text.LocalizedString: But...I don't have a pink hat. Not sure if I'm up for buying one just for this.

Text.SourceString: You hyped for the animal festival tomorrow? I'm kinda into it, but it does kill business for the day...so yeah, it's a mixed bag.
Text.LocalizedString: You hyped for the animal festival tomorrow? I'm kinda into it, but it does kill business for the day...so yeah, it's a mixed bag.

Text.SourceString: Are you ready for our boat trip tomorrow, love? Don't forget to eat something in the morning.//<portrait=annoyed>Trust me, going on an empty stomach...not a cool scene.
Text.LocalizedString: Are you ready for our boat trip tomorrow, love? Don't forget to eat something in the morning.//<portrait=annoyed>Trust me, going on an empty stomach...not a cool scene.

Text.SourceString: Yuri better not flake out on the beach clean-up tomorrow.//It's a whole day thing and, not to curse it, but the way this heat's been, someone might just pass out...
Text.LocalizedString: Yuri better not flake out on the beach clean-up tomorrow.//It's a whole day thing and, not to curse it, but the way this heat's been, someone might just pass out...

Text.SourceString: You've got the greenest thumbs in Coral Island. I mean, look at this farm!
Text.LocalizedString: You've got the greenest thumbs in Coral Island. I mean, look at this farm!

Text.SourceString: Are you taking a break? I could use some company...or a kiss?
Text.LocalizedString: Are you taking a break? I could use some company...or a kiss?

Text.SourceString: This right here is what living on a farm is all about. Connecting with nature, huh, babe?//Chilling on our porch, watching the sun dance around.
Text.LocalizedString: This right here is what living on a farm is all about. Connecting with nature, huh, babe?//Chilling on our porch, watching the sun dance around.

Text.SourceString: That's <PlayerName>$player</>'s farm, baby!
Text.LocalizedString: That's <PlayerName>$player</>'s farm, baby!

Text.SourceString: Everything we grow is so delicious, that's some quality harvest.
Text.LocalizedString: Everything we grow is so delicious, that's some quality harvest.

Text.SourceString: The weather is amazing today, perfect day to be out!
Text.LocalizedString: The weather is amazing today, perfect day to be out!

Text.SourceString: Check out this living room, no dust! I'm so proud of me today.
Text.LocalizedString: Check out this living room, no dust! I'm so proud of me today.

Text.SourceString: The TV was acting up earlier, babe. I was about to take it to <NPCName>Lily</>...she's the tech whizz, right?//Turns out, I forgot to plug in one of the cables. Classic!
Text.LocalizedString: The TV was acting up earlier, babe. I was about to take it to <NPCName>Lily</>...she's the tech whizz, right?//Turns out, I forgot to plug in one of the cables. Classic!

Text.SourceString: Guess who unplugged it in the first place? Yup, it was me, got a little too carried away while cleaning up the place.
Text.LocalizedString: Guess who unplugged it in the first place? Yup, it was me, got a little too carried away while cleaning up the place.

Text.SourceString: How about a foot rub, <PlayerName>$Player</>? You've been on your feet all day.
Text.LocalizedString: How about a foot rub, <PlayerName>$Player</>? You've been on your feet all day.

Text.SourceString: I don't think I've ever slept as soundly as I do here. This house, our farm, it's all so peaceful.
Text.LocalizedString: I don't think I've ever slept as soundly as I do here. This house, our farm, it's all so peaceful.

Text.SourceString: I swapped out the bedding for those silk sheets you like.//<portrait=normal>But fair warning, they're a bit slippery! So watch your step when you're climbing into bed tonight, haha!
Text.LocalizedString: I swapped out the bedding for those silk sheets you like.//<portrait=normal>But fair warning, they're a bit slippery! So watch your step when you're climbing into bed tonight, haha!

Text.SourceString: There's something about the scent in this house...it's so earthy and comforting, must be from our farm.
Text.LocalizedString: There's something about the scent in this house...it's so earthy and comforting, must be from our farm.

Text.SourceString: I try to open the shop every day. Weather permitting, that is.
Text.LocalizedString: I try to open the shop every day. Weather permitting, that is.

Text.SourceString: What a beautiful day to be outdoors.//I might go to Garden Lane before work tomorrow to enjoy my morning beverage and look at the butterflies. Hmm…//<portrait=happy>No, yeah… I will definitely do that.
Text.LocalizedString: What a beautiful day to be outdoors.//I might go to Garden Lane before work tomorrow to enjoy my morning beverage and look at the butterflies. Hmm…//<portrait=happy>No, yeah… I will definitely do that.

Text.SourceString: I’m not too worried about how much the coffee shop makes. Creating the perfect cup of coffee is where my mind is.//Each individual cup. Yeah, every one is special.
Text.LocalizedString: I’m not too worried about how much the coffee shop makes. Creating the perfect cup of coffee is where my mind is.//Each individual cup. Yeah, every one is special.

Text.SourceString: I can’t stand when people wear perfume that’s too strong.//It overwhelms my nose for the day, and I don’t like that.//I like to be able to smell the coffee.
Text.LocalizedString: I can’t stand when people wear perfume that’s too strong.//It overwhelms my nose for the day, and I don’t like that.//I like to be able to smell the coffee.

Text.SourceString: Veggies? Raw ones? Uh, no thanks. That's not my jam, babe. I prefer my food to come from trees, not the ground.
Text.LocalizedString: Veggies? Raw ones? Uh, no thanks. That's not my jam, babe. I prefer my food to come from trees, not the ground.

Text.SourceString: But let me clear the air here: it’s not like I'm on an anti-veggie crusade or something.//I mean, I eat 'em. I do! Not for fun or anything, just the regular, recommended portions.
Text.LocalizedString: But let me clear the air here: it’s not like I'm on an anti-veggie crusade or something.//I mean, I eat 'em. I do! Not for fun or anything, just the regular, recommended portions.

Text.SourceString: Check this out: the coffee maker at the shop is like this super-durable, all-weather champ. Rain, snow, it laughs it off.//Sure, it cost me a pretty penny, but it was a great investment.
Text.LocalizedString: Check this out: the coffee maker at the shop is like this super-durable, all-weather champ. Rain, snow, it laughs it off.//Sure, it cost me a pretty penny, but it was a great investment.

Text.SourceString: My hair gets sticky fast lately. Kinda hate it. Is yours that way too?//I think we need a new shampoo.
Text.LocalizedString: My hair gets sticky fast lately. Kinda hate it. Is yours that way too?//I think we need a new shampoo.

Text.SourceString: The beach isn’t the place to sell coffee. Not freshly brewed, anyway. In cans, yeah, maybe! //<portrait=sad>At the beach, with the wind blowing sand all over… Yeah, no.
Text.LocalizedString: The beach isn’t the place to sell coffee. Not freshly brewed, anyway. In cans, yeah, maybe! //<portrait=sad>At the beach, with the wind blowing sand all over… Yeah, no.

Text.SourceString: For Spring, I usually go for a coffee with floral notes. It seems fitting for the season.
Text.LocalizedString: For Spring, I usually go for a coffee with floral notes. It seems fitting for the season.

Text.SourceString: The coffee shop opened as usual in Winter.//But we closed when it got too cold. Thankfully, those days are behind us now.
Text.LocalizedString: The coffee shop opened as usual in Winter.//But we closed when it got too cold. Thankfully, those days are behind us now.

Text.SourceString: Coffee beans from different regions taste different. Things like soil and weather have an impact.//Correct me if I’m wrong, but I don’t think we can grow <Italic>good</> coffee beans right now, right? In Spring?
Text.LocalizedString: Coffee beans from different regions taste different. Things like soil and weather have an impact.//Correct me if I’m wrong, but I don’t think we can grow <Italic>good</> coffee beans right now, right? In Spring?

Text.SourceString: Not at all, huh? Yeah, that sounds about right.//I didn’t think we could grow coffee here in Spring, not in this weather. Yeah, no.
Text.LocalizedString: Not at all, huh? Yeah, that sounds about right.//I didn’t think we could grow coffee here in Spring, not in this weather. Yeah, no.

Text.SourceString: Will we be planting coffee this Summer, my love?
Text.LocalizedString: Will we be planting coffee this Summer, my love?

Text.SourceString: Sipping hot coffee in the Summer, babe? Now that's the spirit I love!
Text.LocalizedString: Sipping hot coffee in the Summer, babe? Now that's the spirit I love!

Text.SourceString: That's how we roll in this cabin!
Text.LocalizedString: That's how we roll in this cabin!

Text.SourceString: I prefer to brew locally grown beans, of course, but yeah, no. There isn’t much choice, unfortunately.//We can only plant coffee here in Summer. So that means I have to import some of my beans.
Text.LocalizedString: I prefer to brew locally grown beans, of course, but yeah, no. There isn’t much choice, unfortunately.//We can only plant coffee here in Summer. So that means I have to import some of my beans.

Text.SourceString: I don’t drink coffee every day. Yeah, no.//I do enjoy the many different flavors each cup offers. Always a great experience. A mood booster.
Text.LocalizedString: I don’t drink coffee every day. Yeah, no.//I do enjoy the many different flavors each cup offers. Always a great experience. A mood booster.

Text.SourceString: I think Summer is perfect for coffee with citrus notes. Doesn’t Summer feel like a citrusy season to you?
Text.LocalizedString: I think Summer is perfect for coffee with citrus notes. Doesn’t Summer feel like a citrusy season to you?

Text.SourceString: I pay attention to when my customers prefer to have their coffee, and of course, their favorite blend.//For instance, <NPCName>Wakuu</> likes his coffee in the afternoon, and <NPCName>Aaliyah</> likes it early in the morning.
Text.LocalizedString: I pay attention to when my customers prefer to have their coffee, and of course, their favorite blend.//For instance, <NPCName>Wakuu</> likes his coffee in the afternoon, and <NPCName>Aaliyah</> likes it early in the morning.

Text.SourceString: Have you seen the daisies? I’m so tempted to put some in my beard!
Text.LocalizedString: Have you seen the daisies? I’m so tempted to put some in my beard!

Text.SourceString: There’s something about drinking hot chocolate in Fall, isn’t there?//Something special about it.
Text.LocalizedString: There’s something about drinking hot chocolate in Fall, isn’t there?//Something special about it.

Text.SourceString: Every once in a while, I create a coffee omakase, usually in Fall.//I taste-test my favorite combos of the year before putting them on the menu.
Text.LocalizedString: Every once in a while, I create a coffee omakase, usually in Fall.//I taste-test my favorite combos of the year before putting them on the menu.

Text.SourceString: For Fall, you just gotta go with the classic cocoa and caramel notes in your coffee.//It’s perfect for this season.
Text.LocalizedString: For Fall, you just gotta go with the classic cocoa and caramel notes in your coffee.//It’s perfect for this season.

Text.SourceString: Being outdoors has its downside on days like this.
Text.LocalizedString: Being outdoors has its downside on days like this.

Text.SourceString: Can I make you something warm, <PlayerName>$Player</>? I think I might know exactly what you'd like.
Text.LocalizedString: Can I make you something warm, <PlayerName>$Player</>? I think I might know exactly what you'd like.

Text.SourceString: I don’t wear perfume or anything that’s strongly scented, especially when I’m making coffee or blending coffee beans.//Those scents can get into the beans.
Text.LocalizedString: I don’t wear perfume or anything that’s strongly scented, especially when I’m making coffee or blending coffee beans.//Those scents can get into the beans.

Text.SourceString: Living at the inn was an experience, especially during Winter. It got pretty cold.//<portrait=happy>It's so cozy and warm here with you, babe...to be honest, anywhere with you is warm and cozy.
Text.LocalizedString: Living at the inn was an experience, especially during Winter. It got pretty cold.//<portrait=happy>It's so cozy and warm here with you, babe...to be honest, anywhere with you is warm and cozy.

Text.SourceString: Living at the inn was great, especially in Winter. It’s cold, and you just wanna hang out with friends.//Yeah, the inn is cold, and the heater was…questionable at times, but the residents are friendly.
Text.LocalizedString: Living at the inn was great, especially in Winter. It’s cold, and you just wanna hang out with friends.//Yeah, the inn is cold, and the heater was…questionable at times, but the residents are friendly.

Text.SourceString: I don’t like a lot of fuss for my morning coffee, so I’ll usually go for a French press.//Later in the day, I can go for something more complex, like a pour-over or an espresso.
Text.LocalizedString: I don’t like a lot of fuss for my morning coffee, so I’ll usually go for a French press.//Later in the day, I can go for something more complex, like a pour-over or an espresso.

Text.SourceString: The coffee shop is closed when it’s raining like this. So I usually spend the day volunteering at the shelter.
Text.LocalizedString: The coffee shop is closed when it’s raining like this. So I usually spend the day volunteering at the shelter.

Text.SourceString: Out in the rain? Got a place to be?//<portrait=annoyed>Please, don't stay in the rain too long. I wouldn't want you to catch a cold.
Text.LocalizedString: Out in the rain? Got a place to be?//<portrait=annoyed>Please, don't stay in the rain too long. I wouldn't want you to catch a cold.

Text.SourceString: The coffee shop is closed when there’s a storm like this. So I usually spend the day volunteering at the shelter.
Text.LocalizedString: The coffee shop is closed when there’s a storm like this. So I usually spend the day volunteering at the shelter.

Text.SourceString: Out in the storm? Got someplace to be?//<portrait=annoyed>Please, don't stay in the rain too long. I wouldn't want you to catch a cold.
Text.LocalizedString: Out in the storm? Got someplace to be?//<portrait=annoyed>Please, don't stay in the rain too long. I wouldn't want you to catch a cold.

Text.SourceString: Busy as usual, yeah? No rain could slow you down.
Text.LocalizedString: Busy as usual, yeah? No rain could slow you down.

Text.SourceString: Busy as usual, yeah? No snow could slow you down.
Text.LocalizedString: Busy as usual, yeah? No snow could slow you down.

Text.SourceString: Maybe I’ll wear a hat next time. This snow gets my hair all wet.
Text.LocalizedString: Maybe I’ll wear a hat next time. This snow gets my hair all wet.

Text.SourceString: Whew, is it hot or was my coffee too strong? Good gosh, it’s hot! I am <Italic>so</> wired today!//I tried out a new coffee blend, and it hit way harder than I expected!//Don’t think I’ve blinked in the past five minutes! Whew!
Text.LocalizedString: Whew, is it hot or was my coffee too strong? Good gosh, it’s hot! I am <Italic>so</> wired today!//I tried out a new coffee blend, and it hit way harder than I expected!//Don’t think I’ve blinked in the past five minutes! Whew!

Text.SourceString: I’m talking really fast!//I need to sit down.
Text.LocalizedString: I’m talking really fast!//I need to sit down.

Text.SourceString: I love people watching, so owning the coffee stand really is the best job for me.//<portrait=normal>I get to stand here all day and see people go by.
Text.LocalizedString: I love people watching, so owning the coffee stand really is the best job for me.//<portrait=normal>I get to stand here all day and see people go by.

Text.SourceString: Yeah, I get sore feet at the end of the day, but people are interesting. It’s worth it.
Text.LocalizedString: Yeah, I get sore feet at the end of the day, but people are interesting. It’s worth it.

Text.SourceString: When it’s humid, we expect angry clouds.//Beauty never arrives alone. There’s always a price attached.
Text.LocalizedString: When it’s humid, we expect angry clouds.//Beauty never arrives alone. There’s always a price attached.

Text.SourceString: There’s no such thing as weather that’s too hot for drinking hot beverages.//<portrait=annoyed>Drinking coffee is an <Italic>experience</>. You can’t just put <Italic>ice</> in it.//No! Ice waters down the flavor.
Text.LocalizedString: There’s no such thing as weather that’s too hot for drinking hot beverages.//<portrait=annoyed>Drinking coffee is an <Italic>experience</>. You can’t just put <Italic>ice</> in it.//No! Ice waters down the flavor.

Text.SourceString: I think I should get some dog biscuits to keep on the counter.//<portrait=normal>So if people bring their dogs, they can have a treat too.
Text.LocalizedString: I think I should get some dog biscuits to keep on the counter.//<portrait=normal>So if people bring their dogs, they can have a treat too.

Text.SourceString: I saw <NPCName>Taco</> playing around the other day, enjoying the sunny Spring day in the fountain.//<portrait=happy>He sure knows how to have fun!
Text.LocalizedString: I saw <NPCName>Taco</> playing around the other day, enjoying the sunny Spring day in the fountain.//<portrait=happy>He sure knows how to have fun!

Text.SourceString: Oh gosh! I sure hope <NPCName>Taco</> was actually playing in that fountain and not…//Oh good gosh!
Text.LocalizedString: Oh gosh! I sure hope <NPCName>Taco</> was actually playing in that fountain and not…//Oh good gosh!

Text.SourceString: Is it too early to bust out my swimming trunks?//<portrait=normal>Ah, yeah. I can wait till Summer.
Text.LocalizedString: Is it too early to bust out my swimming trunks?//<portrait=normal>Ah, yeah. I can wait till Summer.

Text.SourceString: It’s way too snowy to open the coffee stand.//<portrait=normal>Better stay in close to the fireplace.
Text.LocalizedString: It’s way too snowy to open the coffee stand.//<portrait=normal>Better stay in close to the fireplace.

Text.SourceString: When the snow stops, we can open the coffee shop again, but not now, not today.//Today we relax and give back.
Text.LocalizedString: When the snow stops, we can open the coffee shop again, but not now, not today.//Today we relax and give back.

Text.SourceString: I want to do something fun this Summer.//<portrait=normal>I’m thinking beach day every day!
Text.LocalizedString: I want to do something fun this Summer.//<portrait=normal>I’m thinking beach day every day!

Text.SourceString: That’s what Summer is for!
Text.LocalizedString: That’s what Summer is for!

Text.SourceString: I can’t rely on shipping by sea here.//<portrait=angry>I ordered some coffee beans from San Franciskyo. They were supposed to be here by now, but no cargo boats are coming until next week.
Text.LocalizedString: I can’t rely on shipping by sea here.//<portrait=angry>I ordered some coffee beans from San Franciskyo. They were supposed to be here by now, but no cargo boats are coming until next week.

Text.SourceString: What am I supposed to do? I heard <NpcName>Ben</> can get you the good stuff, even rare finds, but he doesn’t travel much anymore.//I can’t run my business based on <NpcName>Ben’s</> moods.
Text.LocalizedString: What am I supposed to do? I heard <NpcName>Ben</> can get you the good stuff, even rare finds, but he doesn’t travel much anymore.//I can’t run my business based on <NpcName>Ben’s</> moods.

Text.SourceString: Coffee is the perfect drink for people-watching.//It’s a great excuse to sit and observe all the interesting things that are going on.
Text.LocalizedString: Coffee is the perfect drink for people-watching.//It’s a great excuse to sit and observe all the interesting things that are going on.

Text.SourceString: That’s how I fell in love with it – coffee.//<portrait=normal>Well, and people-watching.
Text.LocalizedString: That’s how I fell in love with it – coffee.//<portrait=normal>Well, and people-watching.

Text.SourceString: I’ve always loved the idea of running my own coffee shop, and now I get to do it here, where I can really get to know my customers.
Text.LocalizedString: I’ve always loved the idea of running my own coffee shop, and now I get to do it here, where I can really get to know my customers.

Text.SourceString: I’ve met interesting folks here…through coffee.//<portrait=happy>A hunter, some scientists, a cutie farmer. *winks*
Text.LocalizedString: I’ve met interesting folks here…through coffee.//<portrait=happy>A hunter, some scientists, a cutie farmer. *winks*

Text.SourceString: It isn’t exactly raining money at the coffee shop right now. And gosh, the expenses don’t quit. Rent, beans, payroll. It's bananas!//<portrait=sad>Running the shop is so expensive, sometimes I think about giving it up.
Text.LocalizedString: It isn’t exactly raining money at the coffee shop right now. And gosh, the expenses don’t quit. Rent, beans, payroll. It's bananas!//<portrait=sad>Running the shop is so expensive, sometimes I think about giving it up.

Text.SourceString: I can't help but feel for the folks around here, pre-Coffee Corner era. The lengths they had to go for a decent cup of joe. It's unthinkable.
Text.LocalizedString: I can't help but feel for the folks around here, pre-Coffee Corner era. The lengths they had to go for a decent cup of joe. It's unthinkable.

Text.SourceString: It's like a throwback to my days in San Franciskyo. Not because of any coffee drought, quite the opposite!//<portrait=happy>That place had so many good shops. Never a half-hour walk without hitting a coffee jackpot.
Text.LocalizedString: It's like a throwback to my days in San Franciskyo. Not because of any coffee drought, quite the opposite!//<portrait=happy>That place had so many good shops. Never a half-hour walk without hitting a coffee jackpot.

Text.SourceString: Renting a shop in Starlet Town is pretty affordable.//On paper, it should've been a low-stakes gamble starting my business here, right? But oh boy, the reality is a whole other ballgame.
Text.LocalizedString: Renting a shop in Starlet Town is pretty affordable.//On paper, it should've been a low-stakes gamble starting my business here, right? But oh boy, the reality is a whole other ballgame.

Text.SourceString: Sales aren't exactly skyrocketing here. Even meeting the relatively low rent feels like wrestling a grizzly sometimes.//Tough times, babe. Tough times.
Text.LocalizedString: Sales aren't exactly skyrocketing here. Even meeting the relatively low rent feels like wrestling a grizzly sometimes.//Tough times, babe. Tough times.

Text.SourceString: The best advice I've ever received: Every morning, look in the mirror and be able to say, "Yeah, I like that person staring back at me." That's what living's all about, babe.//Slip into something that makes you feel like a million bucks. Every day's a fresh start, a new runway.
Text.LocalizedString: The best advice I've ever received: Every morning, look in the mirror and be able to say, "Yeah, I like that person staring back at me." That's what living's all about, babe.//Slip into something that makes you feel like a million bucks. Every day's a fresh start, a new runway.

Text.SourceString: Believe it or not, I put in serious thought into what I wear every day. Seriously, I do.//<portrait=happy>Who cares if we're not hitting the red carpet? We gotta feel fly for ourselves. It's all about that "look good, feel good" mantra
Text.LocalizedString: Believe it or not, I put in serious thought into what I wear every day. Seriously, I do.//<portrait=happy>Who cares if we're not hitting the red carpet? We gotta feel fly for ourselves. It's all about that "look good, feel good" mantra

Text.SourceString: Silk clothing is good for this weather. Super breathable, good for your skin.//Gotta make sure your skin – your body – can breathe.//<portrait=happy>A silk pillowcase is a good idea too. Trust me, babe, your hair's gonna thank you.
Text.LocalizedString: Silk clothing is good for this weather. Super breathable, good for your skin.//Gotta make sure your skin – your body – can breathe.//<portrait=happy>A silk pillowcase is a good idea too. Trust me, babe, your hair's gonna thank you.

Text.SourceString: Silk clothing is good for this weather. Super breathable, a treat for your skin. You gotta let your skin, your body, feel the Summer breeze.//<portrait=happy>A silk pillowcase is a good idea too. Trust me, babe, your hair's gonna thank you.
Text.LocalizedString: Silk clothing is good for this weather. Super breathable, a treat for your skin. You gotta let your skin, your body, feel the Summer breeze.//<portrait=happy>A silk pillowcase is a good idea too. Trust me, babe, your hair's gonna thank you.

Text.SourceString: When we get ourselves a new outfit, yeah, it isn’t cheap, babe...but hear me out.//The way I see it, we're gonna be living in these clothes, right? Gotta prioritize comfort, style, and feeling good.
Text.LocalizedString: When we get ourselves a new outfit, yeah, it isn’t cheap, babe...but hear me out.//The way I see it, we're gonna be living in these clothes, right? Gotta prioritize comfort, style, and feeling good.

Text.SourceString: I don’t know where you got that outfit, <PlayerName>$Player</>, but it looks great on you.//<portrait=happy>Good quality fabric, I can tell. Looks warm as heck. Is it a wool blend?
Text.LocalizedString: I don’t know where you got that outfit, <PlayerName>$Player</>, but it looks great on you.//<portrait=happy>Good quality fabric, I can tell. Looks warm as heck. Is it a wool blend?

Text.SourceString: I don’t know where you got that outfit, <PlayerName>$Player</>, but it looks great on you.//<portrait=happy>That fabric, oh heck yeah, that's what I'm talking abuot. Some quality stuff! It screams Summer, and I love it.
Text.LocalizedString: I don’t know where you got that outfit, <PlayerName>$Player</>, but it looks great on you.//<portrait=happy>That fabric, oh heck yeah, that's what I'm talking abuot. Some quality stuff! It screams Summer, and I love it.

Text.SourceString: You know, my love, every time you walk into the shop, my day instantly brightens.//I'm serious, you light up my world.
Text.LocalizedString: You know, my love, every time you walk into the shop, my day instantly brightens.//I'm serious, you light up my world.

Text.SourceString: You have a knack for making people feel comfortable.//It’s a rare and beautiful trait.
Text.LocalizedString: You have a knack for making people feel comfortable.//It’s a rare and beautiful trait.

Text.SourceString: You, my dear, look absolutely stunning.
Text.LocalizedString: You, my dear, look absolutely stunning.

Text.SourceString: Just wrapped up the annual performance reviews for Peet and Gloria. They knocked it out of the park, impressive stuff!//I'm thinking a wage hike is in order next week. They've earned it!
Text.LocalizedString: Just wrapped up the annual performance reviews for Peet and Gloria. They knocked it out of the park, impressive stuff!//I'm thinking a wage hike is in order next week. They've earned it!

Text.SourceString: The one silver lining of Winter is the way it makes folks long for a steaming, cozy cup of java.//That's money in the bank for us, baby!
Text.LocalizedString: The one silver lining of Winter is the way it makes folks long for a steaming, cozy cup of java.//That's money in the bank for us, baby!

Text.SourceString: Winter’s harsh this year, <PlayerName>$Player</>.//Don't worry, I've put out a couple of extra blankets for us.
Text.LocalizedString: Winter’s harsh this year, <PlayerName>$Player</>.//Don't worry, I've put out a couple of extra blankets for us.

Text.SourceString: I tried making snow coffee once.//<portrait=annoyed>Let’s just say it was an…interesting experiment. Yeah, no…
Text.LocalizedString: I tried making snow coffee once.//<portrait=annoyed>Let’s just say it was an…interesting experiment. Yeah, no…

Text.SourceString: I’m not usually a fan of the cold, but there’s something about seeing the first snowfall that makes Winter a bit more bearable.
Text.LocalizedString: I’m not usually a fan of the cold, but there’s something about seeing the first snowfall that makes Winter a bit more bearable.

Text.SourceString: And after that, it's just a chilly downhill ride all the way to Spring.
Text.LocalizedString: And after that, it's just a chilly downhill ride all the way to Spring.

Text.SourceString: Some folks come in here just for the muffins, but I think there’s magic in good coffee and conversation.
Text.LocalizedString: Some folks come in here just for the muffins, but I think there’s magic in good coffee and conversation.

Text.SourceString: That’s what I want this place to be about.
Text.LocalizedString: That’s what I want this place to be about.

Text.SourceString: Our muffins are some of our bestsellers.//I’ve been considering adding some variations, thinking it might boost our sales. Yeah, nah! It didn’t.
Text.LocalizedString: Our muffins are some of our bestsellers.//I’ve been considering adding some variations, thinking it might boost our sales. Yeah, nah! It didn’t.

Text.SourceString: I’ve tried adding various ingredients – berries, bananas, nuts, fish, pumpkin, raisins…//<portrait=surprised>Yeah, raisins! Don’t make that face. It was as bad as it sounds.
Text.LocalizedString: I’ve tried adding various ingredients – berries, bananas, nuts, fish, pumpkin, raisins…//<portrait=surprised>Yeah, raisins! Don’t make that face. It was as bad as it sounds.

Text.SourceString: I like coming here before heading to work.//<portrait=normal>I don’t need to open the shop today. Peet can handle it.
Text.LocalizedString: I like coming here before heading to work.//<portrait=normal>I don’t need to open the shop today. Peet can handle it.

Text.SourceString: This is an excellent spot for reading, isn’t it? A lot of bugs, oh yeah, but it’s <Italic>totally</> worth it.
Text.LocalizedString: This is an excellent spot for reading, isn’t it? A lot of bugs, oh yeah, but it’s <Italic>totally</> worth it.

Text.SourceString: Come sit close, my love... Maybe I can steal a little kiss?
Text.LocalizedString: Come sit close, my love... Maybe I can steal a little kiss?

Text.SourceString: You know, babe... I saw <NpcName>Betty</> filling up the bird feeder in Garden Lane yesterday. She’s there every Monday like clockwork, never misses a week.//I also see <NpcName>Noah</> there <Italic>occasionally</>. Yeah, only occasionally. Not always.
Text.LocalizedString: You know, babe... I saw <NpcName>Betty</> filling up the bird feeder in Garden Lane yesterday. She’s there every Monday like clockwork, never misses a week.//I also see <NpcName>Noah</> there <Italic>occasionally</>. Yeah, only occasionally. Not always.

Text.SourceString: Well, I guess I’m the same, except I just chill, perfecting the art of being a freeloader.//<portrait=normal>I don’t do anything as nice as what <NpcName>Betty</> does.
Text.LocalizedString: Well, I guess I’m the same, except I just chill, perfecting the art of being a freeloader.//<portrait=normal>I don’t do anything as nice as what <NpcName>Betty</> does.

Text.SourceString: There’s a <Italic>buttload</> of beetles and crickets around here, which isn’t exactly ideal.
Text.LocalizedString: There’s a <Italic>buttload</> of beetles and crickets around here, which isn’t exactly ideal.

Text.SourceString: Just last night, I spotted a vibrant blue butterfly. Absolutely mesmerizing.//<portrait=happy>Not here though, it was fluttering outside the window of my home office.
Text.LocalizedString: Just last night, I spotted a vibrant blue butterfly. Absolutely mesmerizing.//<portrait=happy>Not here though, it was fluttering outside the window of my home office.

Text.SourceString: I’ve considered cutting back on the gold-dusted doughnuts with my afternoon tea, but they’re just so…shiny!
Text.LocalizedString: I’ve considered cutting back on the gold-dusted doughnuts with my afternoon tea, but they’re just so…shiny!

Text.SourceString: An outdoor event like live music or poetry readings could be a nice way to bring the community together to enjoy the beautiful Summer, yeah?
Text.LocalizedString: An outdoor event like live music or poetry readings could be a nice way to bring the community together to enjoy the beautiful Summer, yeah?

Text.SourceString: Oh yes, we do have the Animal Festival coming up soon.//Good thought!
Text.LocalizedString: Oh yes, we do have the Animal Festival coming up soon.//Good thought!

Text.SourceString: I spotted this new silk scarf at White Flamingo.//<portrait=concerned>It’s a bit on the pricey side, but the feel of it… So light and airy, just what I need for this Summer heat.
Text.LocalizedString: I spotted this new silk scarf at White Flamingo.//<portrait=concerned>It’s a bit on the pricey side, but the feel of it… So light and airy, just what I need for this Summer heat.

Text.SourceString: Hopefully, tomorrow’s weather will be as clear as today’s.//I’m planning to have my coffee by the creek in Garden Lane.
Text.LocalizedString: Hopefully, tomorrow’s weather will be as clear as today’s.//I’m planning to have my coffee by the creek in Garden Lane.

Text.SourceString: Can you believe I'm rereading Stephen Kang's classic, <Italic>The Sparkling</>? It's this wild ride about...ah, I don't wanna spoil it for you, babe.//Anyway, uh...I must've digested this book at least five times now. Absolute page-turner!
Text.LocalizedString: Can you believe I'm rereading Stephen Kang's classic, <Italic>The Sparkling</>? It's this wild ride about...ah, I don't wanna spoil it for you, babe.//Anyway, uh...I must've digested this book at least five times now. Absolute page-turner!

Text.SourceString: I love waking up at sunrise. The soothing light of a Fall morning on our farm is truly something.//<portrait=happy>We're truly blessed.
Text.LocalizedString: I love waking up at sunrise. The soothing light of a Fall morning on our farm is truly something.//<portrait=happy>We're truly blessed.

Text.SourceString: I’m going to be doing my reading indoors now.//It’s much too cold to relax outside.
Text.LocalizedString: I’m going to be doing my reading indoors now.//It’s much too cold to relax outside.

Text.SourceString: I tried to catch a snowflake on my tongue this morning, bleh!//<portrait=annoyed>Ended up nearly swallowing a whole snowball. Not the breakfast I had in mind.
Text.LocalizedString: I tried to catch a snowflake on my tongue this morning, bleh!//<portrait=annoyed>Ended up nearly swallowing a whole snowball. Not the breakfast I had in mind.

Text.SourceString: Slipped on the ice right outside the shop this morning.//<portrait=surprised>Oh, I didn’t spill my coffee. Yeah, no. Now, that would have been a tragedy!
Text.LocalizedString: Slipped on the ice right outside the shop this morning.//<portrait=surprised>Oh, I didn’t spill my coffee. Yeah, no. Now, that would have been a tragedy!

Text.SourceString: It kind of smells in here, doesn’t it?
Text.LocalizedString: It kind of smells in here, doesn’t it?

Text.SourceString: I told <NpcName>Mark</> about opening a pet café. Now, that’s a good idea!//You serve coffee and let people chill with the animals. Petflix and chill.//<portrait=annoyed>He said no.
Text.LocalizedString: I told <NpcName>Mark</> about opening a pet café. Now, that’s a good idea!//You serve coffee and let people chill with the animals. Petflix and chill.//<portrait=annoyed>He said no.

Text.SourceString: My task today is to mop this place, keeping it clean for my furry friends here.
Text.LocalizedString: My task today is to mop this place, keeping it clean for my furry friends here.

Text.SourceString: Watch out for the puddles over there. It isn’t, errr, water.//<portrait=sad>Somebody had an accident.
Text.LocalizedString: Watch out for the puddles over there. It isn’t, errr, water.//<portrait=sad>Somebody had an accident.

Text.SourceString: <NpcName>Mark</> has demoted me to mop duty now.//He revoked my litter-cleaning privileges after that one incident.
Text.LocalizedString: <NpcName>Mark</> has demoted me to mop duty now.//He revoked my litter-cleaning privileges after that one incident.

Text.SourceString: I mean, who knew you could create a litter box sandstorm just by using a leaf blower for quick cleaning?//<portrait=annoyed>Live and learn, I guess.
Text.LocalizedString: I mean, who knew you could create a litter box sandstorm just by using a leaf blower for quick cleaning?//<portrait=annoyed>Live and learn, I guess.

Text.SourceString: How much do you think it costs to run this place for a year? It can’t be cheap.
Text.LocalizedString: How much do you think it costs to run this place for a year? It can’t be cheap.

Text.SourceString: This place has an odd collection of books. I found one on aliens, one with cookie recipes, one about horses, even one on giant crops.//<portrait=happy>Yeah, no, it’s definitely a quite diverse collection.
Text.LocalizedString: This place has an odd collection of books. I found one on aliens, one with cookie recipes, one about horses, even one on giant crops.//<portrait=happy>Yeah, no, it’s definitely a quite diverse collection.

Text.SourceString: Isn’t the decor in here fab? It has a vintage chic meets antique haven vibe.
Text.LocalizedString: Isn’t the decor in here fab? It has a vintage chic meets antique haven vibe.

Text.SourceString: I’m stepping up my sock game. Style’s not just about shoes and clothes.//<portrait=happy>I’m thinking cashmere-blend socks. <Italic>Beige</>.
Text.LocalizedString: I’m stepping up my sock game. Style’s not just about shoes and clothes.//<portrait=happy>I’m thinking cashmere-blend socks. <Italic>Beige</>.

Text.SourceString: I’m a human popsicle.
Text.LocalizedString: I’m a human popsicle.

Text.SourceString: It’s cold.
Text.LocalizedString: It’s cold.

Text.SourceString: Some of my coffee beans have traveled more than I have.//Imported straight from Patavia, it’s like a vacation in a cup.
Text.LocalizedString: Some of my coffee beans have traveled more than I have.//Imported straight from Patavia, it’s like a vacation in a cup.
